Louis Zara
2417 North 51st Street
Philadelphia, Pennsylvania 19131

 August 11, 1967

Dear Jack,

Art & Lila Weinky, passing through here with their children, came by to lunch with us,

and I asked, as I always do when I encounter Chicago people, "How is Jack Conroy?"

 To my amazement, I was told that you had "retired" and gone back to Moberly!

That's all the info I got, so I thought I'd write you to ask and to reach out and say,
"Hi!" & a guy I've always liked.

 (1) underline Are you well? /underline (Having made Birthday #57 last Wed.,

I began to realize that this is an important question.)

(2) - Are you writing?
(3) - In general, what the hell are you up to?

I'd love to hear from you, Jack!    Yrs.  Lou
Completed

LOUIS ZARA
35 East 35th Street
New York, N.Y. 10016

1/25/76

Dear Jack.

I have been thinking about you much for some reason. I guess I missed your cheery card the holiday past.
 We are [?] the guard that is passing, passing. You are [?] the group (the very small group) I valued.

so I am reaching out to say, "Hi, Jack! How in hell are you?"

 All affection & stuff,    Yrs,  Lou

Mr. Jack Conroy
Completed

in pencil Zeisler, Ernest
Ernest B. Zeisler
179 East Lake shore Drive
Chicago 11, Illinois

 Dec. 9, 1956

Dear Jack:

 Many thanks for your letter of the 26th. I'm very glad you liked the book about Nixon. Yes, I read the

Jewett book in the ngst? edition, which was soon withdrawn and replaced by another with several
very minor corrections. I have always felt that Hiss was almost certainly innocent; but even if he were
guilty, that could not condone the skullduggery of Chambers, Nixon and the FBI for  framing him
and suboring lying, without which he could not have been commited [sic] (even if guilty).

 I completed "Midland Humor" and enjoyed it much; I agree about the Falstaff piece.
 I'll call you one of these days for bd.     Cordially   Ernest
Completed

Monday the 31st at the Pumpkin Patch
Thy Dear Jack -
The feeling for Linus and his belief is even greater today - ! Realizing that - I want to say again how I'll miss the oasis in this desert! 
So good to visit with you Friday evening - and I do look forward to your visits  to Chgo - and do remember - it's a date for

lunch with the Art Dept members! image of finger with string tied around it  remember!

Whenever you can spare the time on your visits to Chgo -
 Take it kinda easy the first week, till you can see the future outlined more clearly.
 I'm underline so /underline grateful to have known you for these eleven (?) years, Jack.

Your friend    Emil
PS  If you don't need the cancelled stamp on the env. save it for me!

1-22-68
EMIL ZUNKER

Hello Jack -

Look at you arrow pointing to photo of 2 men; one of whom is Conroy
in that exciting hat!  so that's what Moberly
has done for you - you old dog!

- But who is that be-knickered gent? - not Don Russell!

God! I hope that when I get to retire that I can Be resplendent
as this!  Even if I have to move to Missouri!
Completed

EMIL ZUNKER

Thanks for your holiday card - and believe me - were [sic] coming to Missouri this summer

sometime - Have folks in St Louis & Wentzville - so we're really going to stop over!

 Our holidays went by very quickly - and New Years went by uneventfully! We finally got

our TV (ordered 2 yr ago) so we stayed close to home in the below zero weather - watched the
youngsters in Chgo loop, on TV screen - they enjoyed the sub-zero I guess - were full of anti
freeze I spose!

 Been very quiet here at 130 - except for the City of Chgo Moving a lot of people to floors

11-13-19 - while theyre [sic] renovating air-cond. the old city Hall - So we get lousier elevator
service than ever!
Completed

EMIL ZUNKER

Haven't had anything exciting since Yvonne had a baby last month - worked till 2 days before

the birth. Saw no pix - no announcement - So have to just believe what I hear.

 Everybody seems to be working hard... lost our artist Dave - haven't replaced him yet. Have

interviewed numerous artists but so far no one fills the bill. so am sending out to free-lance
artists.

 Our Christmas went by so quick - and I finally took our tree down last friday - Now wonder

if the Jan 25 snowstorm of last year will be repeated - here its the 22nd and I'm worried!
You can be glad you weren't here!

 Eugenia still working on cartoons - hoping to hear one of these days that she's been accepted

for some news syndicate.
Completed

EMIL ZUNKER
- oops - just found that I didn't mail your letter -  forgive - forgive!

Here is is Feb 27th already - and Spring underline Must /underline

be starting in Missouri - we have no such thing yet - it has been a long
winter altho it hasnt been zero or blizzard like last year.

 No special news - I wish I could have some news - but just going along at

usual pace      Emil
Completed

2-3-67
Dear Jack -

 Am sure you read & heard and (underline seen /underline on TV) MISSED SO HAPPILY

the snow blizzard we endured here! Suffered yet - too! I wrecked my back removing the snow behind our garage -
a 5 foot drift - with a neighbors snow blower - It got stuck & I tried to dislodge it - when - A-A-wwwk..!
it dislocated my vertebra - So to chiropractor on Sun-Mon & Tues - Back to work on Wed.  Tonite, fri -
will see chiropractor again - and hope he'll take off the tape thats holding me together!

 That we miss you - underline You Know that! /underline
 Never a day goes by - but your illustrious name isn't mentioned!  So underline many /underline

things when happening - we say "Isn't that about what Jack would say (or do)?" or "Wouldn't Jack
underline love /underline to see that?"

 Hope you are enjoying your new surroundings - and finding much to occupy your spare time. (of which we

talented people underline never /underline have enuf!)

 We in Art Dept all say Hello - and We Miss you - and your incomparable sense of humor - etc. etc.     EMIL
Completed

12/11/68
Hello Jack

- Just came across this today - Among the trivia etc. I hauled with me from 130 N. Wells. Hope you

can use it & the negatives can be used for prints or enlargements.

 Your holiday card arrived. Thank you - but ours will be LATE - I'm laid up with Flu-bug & have been

underline MISERABLE /underline of a week now.... - underline blehh! /underline 

 Have been doing free lance work & will start on local bank stationery, masthead etc. - redo all their

printing etc -

 Nothing new - couldn't get to go anywhere this year - oh, well -  See you in '69 for sure!     Emil
Completed

in pencil [1969]
the premises at 1007!

 What a relief to not have the firecrackers blast off at 6 AM as in years ago - t'was

underline Quiet! /underline A few jersk must have bought some bootleg "crackers" &
ka-pow1 during the day & early eve the air & serenity was shattered by these idiots - who 
perhaps don't even own a U.S. flag - much less know what to do with one!

 We had a miserable tough grind here until May which was the deadline for all of "image of cross"

art & photos - worked nites, Sat & Eugenie even came in on Sunday! - a rat race if underline ever
/underline I was in one. Will put me on a hook if I have another spell like - a - that. Of course it
wasn't appreciated - you know how it is - here - but gotta hang on for another 3 1/2 years til 62 -
(Don't know what, underline then /underline - but got a little deal on the fire - can't divulge
it yet - its primative? - but I want underline out /underline at 62 - and get by on a lot less - and
enjoy a few years of doing what I dont have time for now - paint, design, etc
Completed

Not sure  of our trip to the underline South /underline (Missouri -) yet - but will be
in early fall hell its almost that now - the middle of July & all the Summer clearance sales
& me broke! (People tell me if I'd wouldn't squander my $ on those Paris hats etc - I'd be
rich - but then the rich say they're not happy - ! So ?)

 Did you get the Q'ly I sent or are you on the regular mailing list from the Co. Tell me if

you want a binder - 1968 (or no...)

 The place here underline ain't /underline, the same without you - it's underlineglum, /underlinechum!  
  Miss you, Jack - and can only say I'm grateful for those memories of your wit & humor "(peanuts" etc)
 Have a good summer and love to hear underline when /underline you're coming this way -.
    Emil
Completed
